<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Portend" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Portend,</orth> 1) to signify: <cit><quote>what should that alphabetical position p.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 130</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to foreshow; as a bad omen: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.354" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 354</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 113</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.154" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.182" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 182</bibl>. As a good omen: <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.350" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 350</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>